	<entry id="hero_class_name_thorn"><![CDATA[Thorn]]></entry>
	
	<entry id="action_verbose_body_guild_thorn"><![CDATA[Though she has lost her sight, the Thorn compensates with a very sharp sense of hearing. She can easily track her enemies and prevent their attacks, efficiently protecting her allies. When she draws her blade, she recovers her unmatched duelist reflexes, adapting her guard to upcoming opponents. If she manages to read their movements, she will know how to deliver a fatal blow.]]></entry>
    <entry id="action_verbose_body_blacksmith_thorn"><![CDATA[The Thorn's leather outfit, a vestige of her past, protects her while giving complete freedom of movement. Her sword cane is an indispensable asset to her, both her guide and her weapon of choice, an eternal reminder of what she has lost and what she has become.]]></entry>
    <entry id="action_verbose_body_camping_trainer_thorn"><![CDATA[After offering a good sparring session, the Thorn will eventually rest, yet ready to spring awake at a moment's notice. By focusing on the twisted sounds around them, she helps in training her companions to move through the shadows with ease.]]></entry>	
  	
